+
+## Implementation Structure Plan
+
+- Reuse `src/orders/application/OrderService.ts` for cancellation orchestration
+  so authorization, transaction handling, order loading, policy checks, and
+  persistence stay in the public cancellation workflow.
+- Reuse `src/orders/domain/OrderPolicy.ts` for cancellation eligibility. The
+  deadline rule is an order-domain decision, so `canCancelBeforeDeadline()`
+  performs the strict deadline check and `canCancel()` combines it with the
+  order state rule.
+- Keep `src/shared/utils/date.ts` limited to generic date arithmetic. A detached
+  `validateCancellationDeadline()` helper under `shared`, `common`, or generic
+  `utils` is rejected because it would place order business policy outside the
+  order capability.
+- Test deadline boundaries through `OrderService.cancelOrder()` rather than a
+  private helper, proving the public workflow preserves authorization and
+  transaction flow while enforcing before, at, and after deadline behavior.
